Protesters at the Richards Bay Port used bulldozers to flip over a police van and to damage roadside barriers. JOHANNESBURG Protesters at the Richards Bay Port used bulldozers to flip over a police van and to damage roadside barriers.In a video, police fire shots at a bulldozer which then charges at the police.The police can be seen retreating, then the bulldozer proceeds to flip over the police van.The situation at the port entrance turned violent this morning as police fired rubber bullets.The protest is reportedly over working conditions.